metadata.name: bet your bottom dollar
metadata.description:
time was meaningless when we came to this town, we were so young. we lived for the nights, the laughs, the cheers. same places night after night, we had nothing yet we had it all while we thought we could dance and drink away our pain. masters in fooling ourselves, I know that now. but it's good. it's ok who we were.

I left this town without getting what I came for but I finally understood myself. you can bet your bottom dollar we had the time of our lives.  

taken on 35mm color film in chicago, illinois
